It's a great place. It's on a smaller side, so it really depends on the size of your party. We were a party of 16. There was another table approximately the same size, 2 more 4 person tables and a 2 person table over on the side. That setup made the place completely at capacity. The food and service were great! The only qualm I had was the fact that the food had come out with great delays and to all the tables at the same time. For example, the fish came out to all the tables at the same time, there was then a 40 or so min wait till the meat came out. Again all at the same time to all the tables. My guess is that the grill/cooking space is rather small, so they choose to prepare everything at once. Which I understand but it is a bit inconvenient for the guests since we came 1 hr before the second large group and the smaller groups were already there. Otherwise, a very pleasant experience

After celebrating our events at so many others Russian restaurants in B'klyn and NJ, we've decided to try this place for my b-day gathering. Surprisingly, it came out that the food selection and quality are just perfect in every flavor (much better than at some high-advertised places, like Art House, for instance), the service is excellent, the decor and lighting are mood-setting, and the owner goes off his ways to accommodate the customers in every way possible. We'll be back soon!
